1.destruction
the action or process of causing so much damage to something that it no longer exists or cannot be repaired.
2.instruction
a direction or order.
3.distinct
recognizably different in nature from something else of a similar type.
4.compatibility
a state in which two things are able to exist or occur together without problems or conflict.
5.integrate
combine (one thing) with another so that they become a whole.
6.volume
a book forming part of a work or series.
7.backbone
the series of vertebrae extending from the skull to the pelvis; the spine.
8.supply
a stock of a resource from which a person or place can be provided with the necessary amount of that resource.
9.mandatory
required by law or rules; compulsory.
10.decoupled
解耦
11.intentionally
deliberately; on purpose.
12.subsequent
coming after something in time; following.
13.usable
able or fit to be used.
14.Similarly
in a similar way.
15.teardown
an act of completely dismantling something.
16.robust
strong and healthy; vigorous.
17.diverge
(of a road, route, or line) separate from another route, especially a main one, and go in a different direction.
18.boilerplate
rolled steel for making boilers.
19.inherits
receive (money, property, or a title) as an heir at the death of the previous holder.
20.gluing
fasten or join with or as if with glue.
21.delegated
entrust (a task or responsibility) to another person, typically one who is less senior than oneself.
